GUICE IN 6 SIMPLE STEPS (BEGINNER FLOW)

This is all you need to start using Guice in Selenium.

‚úÖ STEP 1: What is Guice? (1 line)

Guice = A simple tool that creates objects for you.
You don‚Äôt write new ClassName() everywhere.

‚úÖ STEP 2: Learn @Inject (1 line)

@Inject ‚Üí "Guice, please give me this object."

Example:

@Inject
WebDriver driver;


You didn't create the driver‚ÄîGuice will.

‚úÖ STEP 3: Learn Module (the brain)

A Module tells Guice HOW to create objects.

Example: tell Guice how to create WebDriver:

public class SeleniumModule extends AbstractModule {
    @Override
    protected void configure() {
        bind(WebDriver.class).toInstance(new ChromeDriver());
    }
}


So now, when you write:

@Inject WebDriver driver;


Guice gives you a ChromeDriver.

‚úÖ STEP 4: Learn @Guice (TestNG-specific)

TestNG needs to know:

"Hey, use Guice injection for this test."

So we write:

@Guice(moduleFactory = SeleniumModuleFactory.class)
public class LoginTest { }

‚úÖ STEP 5: ModuleFactory (TestNG requirement)

ModuleFactory loads your module.

public class SeleniumModuleFactory implements IModuleFactory {
    @Override
    public Module createModule(ITestContext context, Class testClass) {
        return new SeleniumModule();
    }
}


Now TestNG can use Guice.

‚úÖ STEP 6: Use @Inject in the Test
@Guice(moduleFactory = SeleniumModuleFactory.class)
public class LoginTest {

    @Inject
    WebDriver driver;

    @Test
    public void testGoogle() {
        driver.get("https://google.com");
    }
}


You did not write:

new ChromeDriver()


Guice handled it.

üéØ FINAL FLOW SUMMARY (BEGINNER VERSION)
‚úî Step 1 ‚Üí Create Module

Defines how Guice creates WebDriver, Pages, Utilities.

‚úî Step 2 ‚Üí Create ModuleFactory

So TestNG can load Guice module.

‚úî Step 3 ‚Üí Add @Guice to test class

Tells TestNG: ‚ÄúUse Guice DI here.‚Äù

‚úî Step 4 ‚Üí Add @Inject fields

Guice now provides objects automatically.

üß† Your mental model (easy to remember)
@Module       = How objects are created
@Guice        = TestNG enable Guice
@Inject       = Get objects without new


That‚Äôs literally 90% of Guice.